ORM model and JPA 

Basic defination 
wha is ORM ?
ans - Object Relational Mapping (ORM) in JPA is the core mechanism that bridges the gap between object-oriented domain models and relational databases, allowing developers to interact with database tables using Java objects instead of writing raw SQL.  

what is JPA ?
JPA (Java Persistence API) acts as the standard specification that defines the interfaces and annotations (such as @Entity, @Id, and @Table) used to describe this mapping, while ORM implementations like Hibernate, EclipseLink, or OpenJPA provide the actual code that performs the mapping and data persistence

what are the key component of ORM ?

Key Components of JPA ORM
Annotations: JPA uses annotations like @Entity to mark classes as tables, @Id for primary keys, and relationship mappings like @OneToMany or @ManyToOne to define associations between entities. 
Persistence Context: This acts as a cache (similar to an Object Grid) where retrieved entities are stored; changes made to these objects within the same transaction are tracked and synchronized with the database only upon commit. 
CRUD Operations: Developers use the EntityManager interface to perform Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations on entities, which the underlying ORM provider translates into efficient SQL queries. 
Mapping Files: While annotations are common, JPA also supports XML mapping files (orm.xml) to explicitly configure the mapping between Java class attributes and database columns without modifying the source code. 
Relationship Between ORM, JPA, and Implementations
Concept	Role	Examples
ORM	The technique or approach of mapping objects to relational data stores. 	General concept of object-relational mapping.
JPA	The specification (standard) that defines the API and rules for ORM in Java. 	Java Persistence API interfaces and annotations.
Provider	The implementation that executes the JPA specification and handles the heavy lifting. 	Hibernate, EclipseLink, OpenJPA.
By using JPA, developers can write database-independent code, making it easier to switch between different relational databases or ORM providers with minimal code changes, as the JPA standard ensures portability across implementations.

