what are all the configuration that we use for our h2 database or ORM connection with the provider ?

# database connnection properties
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:userDB
spring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.h2.Driver
spring.datasource.username=sa
spring.datasource.password=

# define package to scan
# its completely optional , by default springboot scan for all @Entity but still if we want to scan particular package
spring.jpa.package-to-scan=com.mySpringBoot.entity

# define provider
# its optional , spring automatically picks based on the provider
spring.jpa.properties.javax.persistence.provider=org.hibernate.jpa.HibernatePersistenceProvider
spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.MySQLDialect

# tranction type , default is RESOURCE_LOCAL only
spring.jpa.properties.javax.persistence.transactionType=RESOURCE_LOCAL


what is the meaning if the method is protected ?
A method marked as protected in Java is accessible within its own class, any class in the same package, and subclasses even if they are in different packages.  It cannot be accessed by classes outside the package that are not subclasses. 

Same Package Access: Any class within the same package can access the protected method directly. 
Subclass Access: Subclasses can access the protected method regardless of their package location, allowing for inheritance-based functionality. 
Restriction: Classes outside the package that do not inherit from the class containing the method cannot access it. 
Overriding Rule: When overriding a protected method in a subclass, the overriding method must use either public or protected visibility; it cannot be more restrictive (e.g., private). 
Class Limitation: While methods and variables can be protected, top-level classes and interfaces cannot be declared as protected. 


